The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Bid for venues
Bridgetown: Twelve countries presented bids to host matches in the 2007 cricket World Cup, with St Lucia and Barbados announcing a joint offer on Thursday. As many as eight countries will be allowed to host the matches but the USA, Bermuda and the Bahamas  as non-members of the West Indies Cricket Board  can bid only to host first-round qualifying matches. The venues will be announced on July 12. The joint bid allows the two nations to offer more hotel rooms for the tournament. (AP)  Copyright 
